  "author_association": "MEMBER",
  "body": "When there is an error on startup of TSDB, we don't close the open resources (files, especially m-mapped files). When TSDB is used externally, the resources stay open and can cause mmap explosion (see [cortex#3282](https://github.com/cortexproject/cortex/issues/3282)).\r\n\r\nWe should be gracefully closing the Head and open blocks on startup errors.\r\n\r\nFor anyone looking to tackle this: the fix would go in [this method](https://github.com/prometheus/prometheus/blob/da3ea43242a0a6796c08e7fc55adbdac1a83522d/tsdb/db.go#L556).",
